1
00:00:00,310 --> 00:00:01,710
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,710 --> 00:00:03,480
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,480 --> 00:00:05,240
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:07,710 --> 00:00:08,750
Where do you think you're going?

5
00:00:09,410 --> 00:00:11,880
Watch your manners
when I'm talking to you.

6
00:00:12,180 --> 00:00:14,490
Did your parents raise you
to behave like this?

7
00:00:19,260 --> 00:00:20,260
Seriously?

8
00:00:20,360 --> 00:00:23,360
How dare you glare at me like that?

9
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:25,100
Mom!

10
00:00:25,960 --> 00:00:28,100
Mom, please. Stop.

11
00:00:29,570 --> 00:00:30,740
That's enough!

12
00:00:32,640 --> 00:00:34,510
Who do you think you're shouting at?

13
00:00:35,440 --> 00:00:38,180
Don't you ever
treat Chloe like that again.

14
00:00:38,880 --> 00:00:40,410
What did you just say?

15
00:00:43,780 --> 00:00:44,880
Is this the kind of man you are?

16
00:00:45,550 --> 00:00:47,690
How could you let Chloe
be treated this way?

17
00:00:56,560 --> 00:00:57,960
What do you think you're doing?

18
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:02,370
Who do you think
you're lecturing right now?

19
00:01:03,230 --> 00:01:04,270
Mom!

20
00:01:13,550 --> 00:01:14,550
That's enough.

21
00:01:17,180 --> 00:01:18,720
Mom, please, that's enough.

22
00:01:20,550 --> 00:01:21,920
You insolent brats.

23
00:01:22,620 --> 00:01:25,760
You're finished tomorrow anyway.

24
00:01:26,090 --> 00:01:29,030
You're going to lose the competition
and get thrown out of Adele.

25
00:01:30,460 --> 00:01:31,860
- Let's go.
- You.

26
00:01:31,860 --> 00:01:34,830
Come back if you dare.
You'll regret it.

27
00:01:35,770 --> 00:01:36,770
You little...

28
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:07,530
(Authorized personnel only,
Do not touch)

29
00:02:09,130 --> 00:02:11,240
(Authorized personnel only,
Do not touch)

30
00:02:16,470 --> 00:02:18,380
So this is the ultrapure water.

31
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:24,550
I've basically won
this extra mission.

32
00:02:27,250 --> 00:02:28,250
Who are you?

33
00:02:33,420 --> 00:02:34,630
What brings you here?

34
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:40,900
Hi, Chloe sent me.
We spoke on the phone yesterday.

35
00:02:41,130 --> 00:02:43,230
Right.
You're here for the ultrapure water.

36
00:02:43,540 --> 00:02:45,770
Yes, she told me to be here by six.

37
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:49,510
I'll take this with me, then.

38
00:02:51,480 --> 00:02:52,680
Hold on.

39
00:02:55,480 --> 00:02:56,480
Yes?

40
00:02:57,020 --> 00:02:59,150
May I have your name, please?

41
00:02:59,420 --> 00:03:01,890
I just need to confirm
with Chloe first.

42
00:03:02,490 --> 00:03:03,820
You need to confirm it?

43
00:03:05,420 --> 00:03:07,830
In that case,
could I borrow your phone?

44
00:03:08,090 --> 00:03:10,090
What, my phone?

45
00:03:11,130 --> 00:03:15,670
I was about to contact Chloe myself,
but my phone died.

46
00:03:16,370 --> 00:03:19,540
She's likely in a meeting,
so I was just going to leave a text.

47
00:03:20,570 --> 00:03:22,270
Sure. Go right ahead.

48
00:03:23,140 --> 00:03:24,140
Thank you.

49
00:03:24,440 --> 00:03:28,180
Excuse me,
but I still didn't get your name.

50
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:30,920
Oh, I'm...

51
00:03:32,180 --> 00:03:34,450
It's Choi Mi Rae.

52
00:03:34,750 --> 00:03:35,890
Right, Ms. Choi Mi Rae.

53
00:03:40,190 --> 00:03:41,560
Something urgent came up.

54
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:43,260
Please come by
tomorrow morning instead.

55
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:44,500
(Client: Chloe)

56
00:03:46,460 --> 00:03:47,530
(Delete)

57
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:49,200
(Delete conversation)

58
00:03:51,170 --> 00:03:52,370
(Block contact)

59
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:54,370
(You won't receive calls or messages
from this contact.)

60
00:03:57,710 --> 00:04:00,280
You know, on second thought,

61
00:04:00,450 --> 00:04:02,780
her meeting is probably over by now.

62
00:04:03,450 --> 00:04:05,520
I'll just go to my car
and call her myself.

63
00:04:06,150 --> 00:04:07,720
Right, of course.

64
00:04:08,390 --> 00:04:10,760
I'll make sure she gets this, then.

65
00:04:11,260 --> 00:04:13,020
Sounds good. Drive safe.

66
00:04:13,260 --> 00:04:14,260
Thanks.

67
00:04:19,400 --> 00:04:20,400
Are you okay?

68
00:04:21,570 --> 00:04:22,830
You should worry about yourself.

69
00:04:23,940 --> 00:04:25,400
Does it hurt where she hit you?

70
00:04:25,940 --> 00:04:26,940
I'm fine.

71
00:04:27,640 --> 00:04:28,970
Don't step in like that again.

72
00:04:29,570 --> 00:04:30,810
I can handle it myself.

73
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:33,580
I don't think I can do that.

74
00:04:37,550 --> 00:04:39,420
My heart won't let me,

75
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:41,650
because I haven't given up yet.

76
00:04:50,860 --> 00:04:53,200
I have somewhere to be
for the mission.

77
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:59,170
Why? Is something wrong?

78
00:05:00,070 --> 00:05:03,070
No, it's nothing.
I should get going.

79
00:05:15,420 --> 00:05:18,190
(Ultrapure Water System Room,
Authorized Personnel Only)

80
00:05:18,260 --> 00:05:20,060
They closed up early.

81
00:05:23,830 --> 00:05:25,060
Something urgent came up.

82
00:05:25,060 --> 00:05:26,660
Please come by
tomorrow morning instead.

83
00:05:27,270 --> 00:05:29,630
Is that why he told me
to come by early tomorrow morning?

84
00:05:34,810 --> 00:05:37,110
The person you have called
is unavailable.

85
00:05:37,410 --> 00:05:38,880
- Please try again later.
- What do I do?

86
00:05:40,610 --> 00:05:42,180
Do I have to wait
until tomorrow morning?

87
00:05:56,060 --> 00:05:57,500
Don't look at me like that.

88
00:05:58,060 --> 00:05:59,160
I'm doing all this for you...

89
00:05:59,160 --> 00:06:00,670
You mean for yourself.

90
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:05,840
From now on,
I'm putting myself first.

91
00:06:08,210 --> 00:06:10,070
I'm done letting you
ruin things for me.

92
00:06:12,580 --> 00:06:14,050
Hyun Jun, wait...

93
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:20,450
You really went
and caused trouble...

94
00:06:20,820 --> 00:06:22,490
after ditching me, didn't you?

95
00:06:23,990 --> 00:06:27,460
If I had taken you,
you would've blabbed to Hyun Jun.

96
00:06:29,230 --> 00:06:30,230
Whatever.

97
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:33,260
It'll all be over
by tomorrow anyway.

98
00:06:34,370 --> 00:06:37,900
Chloe will lose the competition
and get kicked out of Adele.

99
00:06:38,440 --> 00:06:40,810
So what if Hyun Jun flips out?
What's he going to do?

100
00:07:08,270 --> 00:07:09,270
Excuse me.

101
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:14,210
Well...

102
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:19,040
Please, you have to help Chloe.

103
00:07:21,350 --> 00:07:23,550
The only person
who can handle this discreetly...

104
00:07:24,580 --> 00:07:26,080
is you, President Kim.

105
00:07:29,420 --> 00:07:30,820
What do you mean by that?

106
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:35,260
What happened?

107
00:07:35,890 --> 00:07:37,860
Is what you told me
on the phone true?

108
00:07:38,260 --> 00:07:39,560
Did you get the ultrapure water?

109
00:07:40,030 --> 00:07:42,700
No. They told me to come pick it up
tomorrow morning.

110
00:07:43,470 --> 00:07:47,510
Then Ms. Choi
must've already intercepted it.

111
00:07:48,270 --> 00:07:50,640
While Oh Jung Ran was stalling you,

112
00:07:50,710 --> 00:07:52,780
Ms. Choi was planning
to make her move.

113
00:07:56,710 --> 00:07:59,180
The person you have called
is unavailable.

114
00:08:02,720 --> 00:08:04,890
Try calling from my phone,
just in case.

115
00:08:12,430 --> 00:08:13,600
Hello?

116
00:08:13,700 --> 00:08:16,330
Director, this is Chloe.

117
00:08:16,900 --> 00:08:18,140
Chloe, of course.

118
00:08:18,470 --> 00:08:20,810
Why are you calling so late?

119
00:08:21,410 --> 00:08:24,480
Is there a problem
with the ultrapure water?

120
00:08:25,580 --> 00:08:28,010
Ms. Choi Mi Rae said
she'd make sure you got it.

121
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:29,750
Choi Mi Rae?

122
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:32,450
But I was told to pick it up
tomorrow morning.

123
00:08:33,250 --> 00:08:36,650
That can't be right.
Ms. Choi already picked it up.

124
00:08:37,620 --> 00:08:42,490
Are you sure you didn't mishear?
Wasn't it Choi Yu Na?

125
00:08:42,790 --> 00:08:45,960
No, I'm sure she said
her name was Choi Mi Rae.

126
00:08:46,730 --> 00:08:48,030
Was she Choi Yu Na?

127
00:08:48,900 --> 00:08:51,070
I'll have to double-check that.

128
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:53,200
I'm sorry to ask,

129
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:56,040
but do you happen to have
any more ultrapure water?

130
00:08:56,210 --> 00:08:58,780
Well, I'm afraid we're out,

131
00:08:58,780 --> 00:09:00,750
and we can't make any more
right now.

132
00:09:01,050 --> 00:09:04,950
There's an issue at the lab,
so I'm working an emergency shift.

133
00:09:05,350 --> 00:09:10,250
The machine broke down,
and everyone's scrambling over here.

134
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:12,390
It broke down?

135
00:09:14,190 --> 00:09:16,030
I see. All right, thank you.

136
00:09:20,800 --> 00:09:23,970
I guess it'll be difficult to get
any ultrapure water right away.

137
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:27,510
Does this mean you'll drop out
of the competition?

138
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:31,680
No.

139
00:09:32,380 --> 00:09:33,840
I won't give up.

140
00:09:47,960 --> 00:09:48,960
You're here early.

141
00:09:50,560 --> 00:09:51,560
Or rather,

142
00:09:52,060 --> 00:09:53,260
did you pull an all-nighter?

143
00:09:54,170 --> 00:09:56,570
Looks like you ran into some trouble
with the mission.

144
00:09:57,670 --> 00:09:58,670
I did.

145
00:09:58,970 --> 00:10:01,210
A so-called "Choi Mi Rae"
who doesn't even exist...

146
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:03,410
swooped in and took what was mine.

147
00:10:07,850 --> 00:10:10,650
Well, you should've kept
a better eye on your things.

148
00:10:11,420 --> 00:10:13,990
You were going
to help me win anyway,

149
00:10:14,250 --> 00:10:15,750
so just think of it as me taking...

150
00:10:15,890 --> 00:10:17,720
what you were going to give me.

151
00:10:55,190 --> 00:10:58,500
All right, let's see
what you've come up with.

152
00:11:02,730 --> 00:11:04,200
Who'd like to begin?

153
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,470
I'll go first.

154
00:11:22,750 --> 00:11:27,090
This is UPW, ultrapure water.

155
00:11:27,690 --> 00:11:30,630
It's pure water
with absolutely no impurities,

156
00:11:30,690 --> 00:11:34,470
used in semiconductor manufacturing
to wash away every speck of dust.

157
00:11:36,970 --> 00:11:38,040
Ultrapure water?

158
00:11:39,340 --> 00:11:41,440
This is the purest water
in the world...

159
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:42,910
that Producer Shin asked for.

160
00:11:43,710 --> 00:11:46,640
Yes. I'm quite familiar
with ultrapure water.

161
00:11:47,410 --> 00:11:48,850
That must've been difficult
to get your hands on.

162
00:11:49,180 --> 00:11:52,520
I have to be this capable
if I want to work with you.

163
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:55,920
Weren't you also testing us on that?

164
00:11:56,620 --> 00:11:59,660
Exactly. You understood
my intentions perfectly.

165
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:10,770
I suppose it's my turn now.

166
00:12:11,700 --> 00:12:15,910
Let's see the water
you've brought as well, Chloe.

167
00:12:43,670 --> 00:12:44,770
A pearl?

168
00:12:45,970 --> 00:12:47,770
That's not water.

169
00:12:49,240 --> 00:12:51,210
Did you misunderstand
the assignment?

170
00:12:52,210 --> 00:12:55,450
Wait. You were told to find water,

171
00:12:55,950 --> 00:12:57,750
so why did you bring a pearl?

172
00:12:59,450 --> 00:13:01,550
I'm sure she has her reasons.

173
00:13:06,220 --> 00:13:10,130
Why do you think
we need the purest water?

174
00:13:11,530 --> 00:13:15,030
Isn't it because it can remove
even the smallest impurities?

175
00:13:16,330 --> 00:13:18,670
So I decided to find water...

176
00:13:18,940 --> 00:13:22,440
that can truly cleanse
the human heart.

177
00:13:27,180 --> 00:13:29,510
Maybe it's not really
about the water.

178
00:13:30,110 --> 00:13:33,150
If you can't get
ultrapure water right now,

179
00:13:33,880 --> 00:13:37,390
rethink why you were asked
to find the purest water...

180
00:13:37,450 --> 00:13:40,960
and what it really means,
because it's your only option.

181
00:13:42,230 --> 00:13:43,360
The intent...

182
00:13:43,860 --> 00:13:44,960
or the meaning behind it?

183
00:13:53,300 --> 00:13:55,410
(1. What is ultrapure water?)

184
00:14:04,550 --> 00:14:09,220
Ms. Kim, what do you think is
the purest water in the world?

185
00:14:11,160 --> 00:14:12,160
Let's see.

186
00:14:12,590 --> 00:14:15,890
Does having no impurities
always mean something is pure?

187
00:14:16,390 --> 00:14:17,560
I suggest thinking...

188
00:14:17,960 --> 00:14:20,460
about the meaning of "pure,"
not the water itself.

189
00:14:22,230 --> 00:14:25,270
Imagine the most difficult thing
to wash clean.

190
00:14:25,770 --> 00:14:29,440
Wouldn't the best water be
whatever can cleanse that?

191
00:14:30,310 --> 00:14:32,680
The hardest thing to wash clean?

192
00:14:32,940 --> 00:14:35,180
I believe
nothing is harder to cleanse...

193
00:14:35,180 --> 00:14:37,180
than the human heart.

194
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:40,920
A long time ago, my heart...

195
00:14:41,750 --> 00:14:45,120
was filled with despair
that felt impossible to wash away.

196
00:14:45,620 --> 00:14:49,160
But then,
someone's heartfelt tears...

197
00:14:50,260 --> 00:14:52,160
washed that despair away.

198
00:15:03,240 --> 00:15:05,080
Saving you will give me strength,

199
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:08,480
and I need that strength
to protect my child too.

200
00:15:09,010 --> 00:15:10,450
Help me do that, Dan Hui.

201
00:15:15,490 --> 00:15:16,690
Come to think of it,

202
00:15:17,390 --> 00:15:21,260
I'm still relying on those tears
to keep living, even now.

203
00:15:23,190 --> 00:15:26,760
Chloe, what is it
that you most want to wash away?

204
00:15:37,140 --> 00:15:40,940
Everyone has something
they want to wash from their heart.

205
00:15:42,080 --> 00:15:45,380
For some, it's despair.

206
00:15:46,250 --> 00:15:48,520
For others, desire.

207
00:15:50,650 --> 00:15:52,560
Maybe even shame.

208
00:15:54,460 --> 00:15:58,200
For someone else,
it could be a painful past.

209
00:16:03,870 --> 00:16:07,070
The purest water,
capable of washing all of that away,

210
00:16:07,870 --> 00:16:10,140
is, I believe, a heartfelt tear.

211
00:16:11,510 --> 00:16:15,380
That is why I brought a pearl
called the tear of the ocean.

212
00:16:16,610 --> 00:16:17,680
That's a nice sentiment.

213
00:16:19,920 --> 00:16:20,920
But still,

214
00:16:21,250 --> 00:16:22,950
she's strayed too far
from the topic.

215
00:16:23,250 --> 00:16:25,790
We were told
to bring Producer Shin water.

216
00:16:26,560 --> 00:16:28,860
Was it really only about the water?

217
00:16:29,890 --> 00:16:32,460
You just said it yourself, Ms. Choi.

218
00:16:33,160 --> 00:16:37,570
You said he also wanted to see
if you could get something rare.

219
00:16:39,440 --> 00:16:41,440
Maybe Chloe
has a different ability...

220
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:43,470
that goes beyond just bringing water
as instructed.

221
00:16:43,570 --> 00:16:44,610
Ma'am.

222
00:16:45,380 --> 00:16:48,150
You're just taking her side
because you want her to win.

223
00:16:49,350 --> 00:16:51,950
I wanted to show
I can go beyond form...

224
00:16:52,520 --> 00:16:56,590
and find deeper meaning
beneath the surface.

225
00:16:58,020 --> 00:17:01,360
Being a producer is also
about discovering new meaning,

226
00:17:02,090 --> 00:17:05,530
and you have a hidden side as well.

227
00:17:06,060 --> 00:17:07,060
Excuse me?

228
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:11,400
I'm talking about the relationship
Ms. Choi called an affair.

229
00:17:13,300 --> 00:17:16,610
The truth is,
you were helping someone...

230
00:17:16,710 --> 00:17:18,510
suffering from domestic abuse.

231
00:17:20,710 --> 00:17:21,850
How did you know that?

232
00:17:22,310 --> 00:17:25,320
I wanted to know what kind of person
I'd be working with.

233
00:17:26,080 --> 00:17:29,450
I wanted to know the truth,
not the salacious rumors.

234
00:17:30,820 --> 00:17:34,260
And thanks to that,
I learned who you really are.

235
00:17:35,360 --> 00:17:36,360
Only then...

236
00:17:36,430 --> 00:17:39,800
would I have earned the right
to work with you.

237
00:17:43,930 --> 00:17:47,540
All right, now that we've heard
both presentations,

238
00:17:47,810 --> 00:17:48,970
let's make our decision.

239
00:17:51,280 --> 00:17:53,740
Producer Shin's task was clearly
about water.

240
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:56,080
No matter how deep the meaning,

241
00:17:56,280 --> 00:17:59,520
straying from the topic
is just an excuse.

242
00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:00,920
Just an excuse, you say?

243
00:18:01,820 --> 00:18:03,050
Yes, I agree.

244
00:18:19,900 --> 00:18:21,100
Aren't we late?

245
00:18:21,540 --> 00:18:23,410
I have to see the results in person.

246
00:18:23,470 --> 00:18:25,710
Actually, it's better if we're late
and don't go in.

247
00:18:26,310 --> 00:18:29,380
How can you be so shameless
after betraying your only son?

248
00:18:30,550 --> 00:18:31,780
Did you call me shameless?

249
00:18:31,780 --> 00:18:34,150
Instead of helping your only son,
you...

250
00:18:35,450 --> 00:18:36,620
Zip it.

251
00:18:37,250 --> 00:18:40,020
Good parenting isn't about
giving your child whatever they want.

252
00:18:40,090 --> 00:18:42,790
Sometimes you have to get rid of
what's harmful to them.

253
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:48,330
That Chloe girl never had
any real feelings for Hyun Jun.

254
00:18:49,630 --> 00:18:52,440
How could I support a girl
who wants to marry him without love?

255
00:18:52,940 --> 00:18:56,510
For Hyun Jun, getting rid of her
is absolutely the right thing to do.

256
00:18:56,570 --> 00:18:59,410
Of course,
because you're always right.

257
00:18:59,610 --> 00:19:00,840
You never listen to anyone else.

258
00:19:02,250 --> 00:19:06,950
I hate to see the disappointed look
on Hyun Jun's face,

259
00:19:08,090 --> 00:19:10,790
so you can go in and enjoy the show.

260
00:19:13,690 --> 00:19:15,830
Fine. We'll see.

261
00:19:16,460 --> 00:19:18,700
See who was right in the end!

262
00:19:25,370 --> 00:19:26,870
I'll now announce the results.

263
00:19:27,740 --> 00:19:30,240
I choose Ms. Choi Yu Na...

264
00:19:30,240 --> 00:19:31,440
Police.

265
00:19:38,450 --> 00:19:39,820
What's going on?

266
00:19:39,820 --> 00:19:41,550
We're here for Choi Yu Na.

267
00:19:47,390 --> 00:19:48,430
Ms. Choi Yu Na.

268
00:19:48,990 --> 00:19:51,530
You entered the CX Lab last night,
correct?

269
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:53,600
What?

270
00:19:55,500 --> 00:19:56,500
I didn't.

271
00:19:56,500 --> 00:19:59,170
The records show
you entered as Choi Mi Rae.

272
00:19:59,470 --> 00:20:01,940
If you keep lying,
it'll only hurt your case.

273
00:20:02,240 --> 00:20:05,140
Are you certain
you didn't enter the lab?

274
00:20:06,240 --> 00:20:07,640
I just...

275
00:20:11,680 --> 00:20:14,150
What business
do the police have here?

276
00:20:15,490 --> 00:20:16,790
Start by explaining yourselves.

277
00:20:17,020 --> 00:20:18,520
There was
an equipment-related accident...

278
00:20:18,520 --> 00:20:19,820
at the CX Lab last night.

279
00:20:20,220 --> 00:20:23,560
Circumstantial evidence links
Ms. Choi to the accident.

280
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:27,360
We need you to come with us
to the station for questioning.

281
00:20:27,800 --> 00:20:29,030
An equipment-related accident?

282
00:20:29,870 --> 00:20:31,030
I know nothing about it.

283
00:20:31,030 --> 00:20:33,000
All I took was this ultrapure water.

284
00:20:37,440 --> 00:20:41,780
I knew it.
You stole my ultrapure water.

285
00:20:41,910 --> 00:20:44,750
Did you just steal
someone else's hard work again?

286
00:20:45,980 --> 00:20:48,850
Some people never change.

287
00:20:52,990 --> 00:20:54,390
Given the circumstances,

288
00:20:54,690 --> 00:20:56,890
Chloe should win the competition.

289
00:20:56,890 --> 00:20:59,000
Yes, I agree.

290
00:20:59,360 --> 00:21:00,360
No.

291
00:21:01,030 --> 00:21:04,230
No, I was supposed to win. I won!

292
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:08,770
All right, that concludes
the final mission. Follow me.

293
00:21:10,410 --> 00:21:11,580
Sir!

294
00:21:12,110 --> 00:21:13,240
Sir!

295
00:21:14,380 --> 00:21:15,550
Sir!

296
00:21:20,350 --> 00:21:22,420
I told you I'd help you.

297
00:21:23,450 --> 00:21:27,460
If you'd just trusted me and waited,
you would've won.

298
00:21:27,520 --> 00:21:28,830
Stop lying.

299
00:21:29,660 --> 00:21:31,060
From the very beginning,

300
00:21:31,900 --> 00:21:33,800
you only ever planned to win.

301
00:21:34,460 --> 00:21:36,170
You still don't trust me, do you?

302
00:21:36,730 --> 00:21:39,070
Then I guess
there's nothing I can do.

303
00:21:51,050 --> 00:21:52,050
Hey, wait.

304
00:21:53,280 --> 00:21:56,250
What's with you? You lost?
You said you could win.

305
00:21:56,350 --> 00:21:58,960
You said all I had to do
was keep Chloe busy.

306
00:21:59,390 --> 00:22:01,990
I helped because you said this would
be the end of it, and you blew it.

307
00:22:02,190 --> 00:22:06,160
How dare you ruin my son's life
by being the worst thief ever?

308
00:22:06,700 --> 00:22:07,960
How will you make up for this?

309
00:22:07,960 --> 00:22:09,800
Let go of me.

310
00:22:10,370 --> 00:22:13,600
How is it my fault
that your son's life is falling apart?

311
00:22:13,870 --> 00:22:16,410
What did you just say?

312
00:22:17,610 --> 00:22:18,880
Ms. Oh!

313
00:22:20,640 --> 00:22:22,610
Did you meddle again this time?

314
00:22:23,010 --> 00:22:24,680
Were you acting hysterical
around Chloe...

315
00:22:25,550 --> 00:22:27,150
on purpose?

316
00:22:27,420 --> 00:22:31,620
I wasn't meddling.
I was trying to be your shield.

317
00:22:32,260 --> 00:22:33,990
I can't just stand by
and watch my only son...

318
00:22:33,990 --> 00:22:35,690
get conned into marriage.

319
00:22:36,260 --> 00:22:38,830
I know that witch doesn't love you.

320
00:22:38,830 --> 00:22:40,400
Enough!

321
00:22:41,730 --> 00:22:43,330
Let go of me.

322
00:22:45,900 --> 00:22:47,140
Choi Yu Na.

323
00:22:49,370 --> 00:22:51,310
Did you really cause this mess?

324
00:22:54,950 --> 00:22:56,010
Or was it...

325
00:23:01,250 --> 00:23:02,320
Good.

326
00:23:03,920 --> 00:23:05,590
I trust there won't be any problems.

327
00:23:06,190 --> 00:23:09,930
Yes, sir. Once the investigation
officially begins,

328
00:23:10,260 --> 00:23:13,330
Choi Yu Na will be framed
as the culprit.

329
00:23:13,660 --> 00:23:16,570
She'll face criminal charges
and a civil suit for damages.

330
00:23:17,870 --> 00:23:19,200
The whole situation will escalate.

331
00:23:20,540 --> 00:23:21,840
Excellent.

332
00:23:22,710 --> 00:23:25,410
Looks like everything's
falling into place.

333
00:23:42,830 --> 00:23:44,360
What now?

334
00:23:45,460 --> 00:23:47,530
Are you going to break
something else?

335
00:23:55,510 --> 00:23:57,110
What's going on?

336
00:23:57,110 --> 00:23:59,110
Mom. Ms. Oh.

337
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:03,180
Anyway, Chloe won,

338
00:24:04,580 --> 00:24:05,880
and we're going to get married.

339
00:24:07,150 --> 00:24:09,450
No, that's the problem.

340
00:24:09,450 --> 00:24:11,560
She doesn't have feelings for you.

341
00:24:14,620 --> 00:24:16,730
Her heart can come last.

342
00:24:18,800 --> 00:24:20,630
Wait, what?

343
00:24:21,330 --> 00:24:22,530
I want her.

344
00:24:24,900 --> 00:24:28,470
The place by Chloe's side,
the title of being her husband,

345
00:24:30,040 --> 00:24:33,680
her touch, her gaze, everything.
All of it.

346
00:24:33,880 --> 00:24:34,910
Her heart?

347
00:24:38,580 --> 00:24:40,150
Her heart can come last.

348
00:24:41,690 --> 00:24:43,020
Even if that's how it is,

349
00:24:44,890 --> 00:24:46,620
she's the woman I have to have.

350
00:24:53,700 --> 00:24:54,830
Are you saying...

351
00:24:55,600 --> 00:24:56,900
you don't love her?

352
00:24:57,600 --> 00:24:58,840
You just want to own her?

353
00:25:00,170 --> 00:25:02,310
I guess that's my kind of love.

354
00:25:04,370 --> 00:25:06,740
Help me get Chloe,

355
00:25:08,950 --> 00:25:10,950
and I'll help you get...

356
00:25:12,350 --> 00:25:13,880
what you want in return.

357
00:25:27,700 --> 00:25:29,730
So, you won after all.

358
00:25:30,530 --> 00:25:33,770
- Congratulations.
- I owe it to you, President Kim.

359
00:25:33,940 --> 00:25:35,110
You did well.

360
00:25:35,470 --> 00:25:38,140
I won't be thanking you, though.

361
00:25:38,780 --> 00:25:40,540
After all, you got what you wanted.

362
00:25:40,540 --> 00:25:43,950
Your son is now free
from a marriage he didn't want.

363
00:25:49,190 --> 00:25:51,590
And what about you, Chloe?

364
00:25:52,260 --> 00:25:54,930
Are you going to marry
Director Park Hyun Jun?

365
00:25:56,360 --> 00:25:59,800
- Mother.
- My marriage isn't your concern.

366
00:26:02,570 --> 00:26:03,570
Well, then...

367
00:26:08,710 --> 00:26:10,910
Chloe's always so cold, isn't she?

368
00:26:13,810 --> 00:26:18,720
I'll be on my way.
I'll leave you two to talk.

369
00:26:27,960 --> 00:26:31,430
You're finally free
from that unwanted marriage.

370
00:26:33,500 --> 00:26:36,130
Now you just need to get over Chloe.

371
00:26:36,470 --> 00:26:39,600
No. That marriage
between Chloe and Hyun Jun?

372
00:26:39,940 --> 00:26:41,040
I'm going to stop it.

373
00:26:41,240 --> 00:26:42,240
Min Jun.

374
00:26:42,240 --> 00:26:45,180
When I win her back,
please give us your blessing.

375
00:26:45,380 --> 00:26:47,780
I'll make it quick,
so it won't take long.

376
00:26:47,880 --> 00:26:49,180
Don't bother.

377
00:26:49,980 --> 00:26:53,280
I won't give you my blessing
for any reason.

378
00:26:53,320 --> 00:26:54,320
No.

379
00:26:54,920 --> 00:26:56,950
You'll have no choice
but to give us your blessing.

380
00:27:15,640 --> 00:27:17,710
What happened to Choi Yu Na?

381
00:27:19,410 --> 00:27:20,810
According to the police,

382
00:27:21,950 --> 00:27:25,120
she intercepted the ultrapure water
and sabotaged the lab equipment.

383
00:27:25,550 --> 00:27:28,950
If intent is proven,
she'll face criminal charges.

384
00:27:29,790 --> 00:27:33,390
And even if it was an accident,
she'll still face civil liability.

385
00:27:33,890 --> 00:27:36,190
Either way,
she's in a lot of trouble.

386
00:27:38,730 --> 00:27:39,730
I think...

387
00:27:40,630 --> 00:27:42,830
Choi Yu Na was framed.

388
00:27:44,330 --> 00:27:45,340
Framed?

389
00:27:51,210 --> 00:27:53,110
I came in for questioning,

390
00:27:53,110 --> 00:27:54,980
so why did you lock me up?

391
00:27:55,680 --> 00:27:57,580
I told you I didn't do anything.

392
00:27:58,280 --> 00:27:59,520
Quiet down.

393
00:28:05,720 --> 00:28:10,630
Sir, you came to see me, right?
Please, you have to help me.

394
00:28:10,760 --> 00:28:13,700
They said it was just questioning,
but now they've locked me up...

395
00:28:13,760 --> 00:28:14,930
That's because...

396
00:28:15,370 --> 00:28:16,830
during the investigation,

397
00:28:17,500 --> 00:28:19,440
they found conclusive evidence.

398
00:28:22,070 --> 00:28:23,070
Evidence?

399
00:28:24,140 --> 00:28:25,380
Damage the machine...

400
00:28:26,210 --> 00:28:27,210
and plant...

401
00:28:28,780 --> 00:28:30,780
these fingerprints on the computer.

402
00:28:32,220 --> 00:28:33,420
Understood.

403
00:28:35,350 --> 00:28:38,420
Ms. Choi, your prints were found
on the computer.

404
00:28:39,160 --> 00:28:40,490
Your status has been changed...

405
00:28:41,090 --> 00:28:42,730
from voluntary questioning
to emergency arrest,

406
00:28:43,160 --> 00:28:44,360
and you're being charged
with property damage...

407
00:28:44,360 --> 00:28:45,560
and obstruction of business.

408
00:28:45,900 --> 00:28:46,900
This is ridiculous.

409
00:28:47,400 --> 00:28:50,170
I never even touched the computer.
This has to be a mistake.

410
00:28:52,500 --> 00:28:55,870
Please, get me out of here.
You're powerful enough to do it.

411
00:28:58,110 --> 00:29:01,240
Don't forget
I have leverage over you.

412
00:29:03,080 --> 00:29:07,080
Ms. Choi, think about
the situation you're in.

413
00:29:08,550 --> 00:29:10,220
Even if you expose me from in there,

414
00:29:13,190 --> 00:29:15,590
what good would that do you?

415
00:29:16,630 --> 00:29:19,860
You'd only be taking us all down.
Seriously.

416
00:29:21,970 --> 00:29:25,000
Look, this is no time for threats.

417
00:29:25,300 --> 00:29:26,640
You should be...

418
00:29:27,070 --> 00:29:29,470
begging me to help you.

419
00:29:31,240 --> 00:29:33,510
Then please, I'm asking.

420
00:29:34,110 --> 00:29:35,850
I'm telling you, this is a setup.

421
00:29:38,210 --> 00:29:39,220
All right.

422
00:29:40,280 --> 00:29:43,820
Now that you're begging for my help,
I can't just ignore you.

423
00:29:46,320 --> 00:29:47,320
But...

424
00:29:49,560 --> 00:29:52,560
it's going to cost you.

425
00:29:54,660 --> 00:29:55,830
What do you mean?

426
00:30:02,610 --> 00:30:04,070
Hand over the recording.

427
00:30:06,210 --> 00:30:07,210
Sir.

428
00:30:08,410 --> 00:30:10,480
Hand over the recording,

429
00:30:12,280 --> 00:30:13,980
and I'll make this all go away.

430
00:30:19,190 --> 00:30:22,130
I think Chairman Park is the one
who set her up.

431
00:30:23,160 --> 00:30:26,360
He's trying to get the recording
Choi Yu Na has on him.

432
00:30:27,930 --> 00:30:29,430
Yes, of course.

433
00:30:30,670 --> 00:30:32,970
Then if we get
the recording first...

434
00:30:32,970 --> 00:30:33,970
No.

435
00:30:34,700 --> 00:30:38,240
I'm going after something
more important than the recording.

436
00:30:39,810 --> 00:30:40,880
Something more important?

437
00:30:47,750 --> 00:30:50,320
I'll never give you the recording.

438
00:30:52,260 --> 00:30:55,020
Then you'll be ruining your life.

439
00:30:56,530 --> 00:30:59,200
You've already lost your job
and the chance to marry Min Jun.

440
00:31:00,930 --> 00:31:03,130
That just makes it easier
to destroy your life.

441
00:31:04,000 --> 00:31:06,400
If you don't want to rot away
in a cell,

442
00:31:07,900 --> 00:31:10,440
hand over the recording.

443
00:31:11,210 --> 00:31:12,280
My marriage,

444
00:31:12,780 --> 00:31:13,780
my job,

445
00:31:13,880 --> 00:31:16,380
the recording, and even my own life?

446
00:31:19,180 --> 00:31:20,780
I'm not giving any of it up.

447
00:31:30,430 --> 00:31:33,930
Resentment, betrayal, and...

448
00:31:35,400 --> 00:31:36,400
hatred.

449
00:31:38,430 --> 00:31:39,970
I'm going to harness...

450
00:31:40,470 --> 00:31:42,510
Choi Yu Na's hatred for Park Tae Ho.

451
00:31:44,170 --> 00:31:45,440
So that a desire...

452
00:31:46,340 --> 00:31:48,380
to destroy Park Tae Ho...

453
00:31:49,150 --> 00:31:50,750
can take root in her.

454
00:32:33,220 --> 00:32:36,260
(Pearl in Red)

455
00:32:36,360 --> 00:32:37,660
You must be pretty nervous...

456
00:32:37,660 --> 00:32:39,330
if you're following me
around everywhere.

457
00:32:39,800 --> 00:32:42,470
Too bad. I have no intention
of calling off this wedding.

458
00:32:42,630 --> 00:32:43,700
What are you doing?

459
00:32:44,000 --> 00:32:45,770
This isn't what we agreed on.

460
00:32:45,770 --> 00:32:48,570
Was this your plan from the start?

461
00:32:49,010 --> 00:32:51,210
- Sir!
- Take a look at this.

462
00:32:51,340 --> 00:32:52,980
Is there anything else
about Oh Jung Ran's past?

463
00:32:52,980 --> 00:32:55,410
Did you tell Myung Hui
about Munhwadang?

464
00:32:56,950 --> 00:32:58,850
Kim Myung Hui couldn't have,
could she?

465
00:32:59,580 --> 00:33:01,520
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
